items.title: AOL Will End Its Dial-Up Internet Service (Yes, It’s Still Operating)
items.description: The company said the service, synonymous with the early days of the internet, will be discontinued on Sept. 30.

items.title: A Sidelined Zelensky Warns That Russia Will Try to Deceive the U.S.
items.description: Ukraine fears that the Kremlin will try to convince President Trump at U.S.-Russian talks in Alaska that Ukraine, not Russia, is the obstacle to peace...

items.title: Trump Prepares to Meet Putin, and Al Jazeera Says Israel Killed Its Journalists in Gaza
Israel’s Plan for Gaza City Is Still Unclear
items.description: The Israeli government said last week that it wanted to capture Gaza City, but how and when it will proceed has yet to be decided.

items.title: Mamdani Will Visit 5 Boroughs on Anti-Trump Tour
items.description: Zohran Mamdani, the Democratic candidate for mayor, will seek to highlight the ways he believes President Trump’s agenda hurts New York City.
